**Step 3: Choose One or More Elements of the System to Refine**

The elements selected for refinement are:

|Subsystem|Rationale for Refinement|
| :- | :- |
|Conversation Service & AI Orchestrator|Core to UC-1; handles latency, AI model integration, and personalization.|
|Dashboard Service & Integration Facade|Enables UC-2; validates cross-system data composition and real-time updates.|
|Sync & Recovery Worker|Supports UC-7; focuses on resilience and availability attributes.|

-----
**Step 4: Choose Design Concepts That Satisfy the Selected Drivers**

|Design Decision & Location|Rationale / QA Addressed|
| :- | :- |
|Use event-driven communication between Core Services and Integration Layer|Async message queues (Kafka topics) reduce latency and decouple services (QA-1, QA-2).|
|Introduce a Caching Layer (Edge & Model Responses)|Frequently asked queries and AI inferences are cached to improve response time (QA-1).|
|Implement Bulk and Incremental Sync Processes for Adapters|Reduces load on external systems and supports fail-safe recovery (QA-2, UC-7).|
|Adopt a Policy-based Access Control Module|Provides fine-grained authorization for different user roles (QA-3).|
|Use WebSocket / GraphQL Subscriptions for Real-Time Updates|Keeps the Dashboard interactive without constant polling (QA-1, UC-2).|
|Implement Circuit-Breaker & Retry Pattern in Integration Adapters|Ensures resilience to external API failures (QA-2, UC-7).|
|Use Auto-Scaler Policies per Service (Predictive Scaling)|Maintains throughput under 5 000 concurrent users (QA-4).|

Discarded alternatives include direct HTTP calls between services (synchronous coupling), manual batch syncs, and centralized monolithic auth —all rejected for scalability and maintainability reasons.

-----


**Step 5: Instantiate Architectural Elements and Define Interfaces**

UC-1 – Ask Question Flow

1. User sends a text or voice query → BFF layer → API Gateway.
1. Gateway authenticates via SSO and forwards to Conversation Service.
1. Conversation Service checks Response Cache; if miss, calls AI Orchestrator.
1. AI Orchestrator assembles prompt with user context from Profile Service and embeddings from Vector Store.
1. AI Orchestrator invokes Model Endpoint and returns response.
1. Conversation Service records interaction (audit & personalization) and returns answer to client.

UC-2 – Personalized Dashboard Flow

1. User accesses Dashboard → Dashboard Service aggregates data through Integration Facade.
1. Integration Facade invokes LMS, Registration, and Calendar adapters in parallel via async calls.
1. Results merged and cached; Dashboard Service sends consolidated view to client via GraphQL.
1. GraphQL Subscriptions push updates on course changes or new announcements.

UC-7 – Data Sync & Recovery Flow

1. Sync & Recovery Worker triggers periodically (via scheduler or event signal).
1. Fetches delta changes from external systems using cursor-based pagination.
1. Applies idempotent upserts to Operational DB and Vector Store.
1. On failure, Circuit-Breaker opens; failed items sent to retry queue.
1. System sends alerts to Analytics Service and Admin Dashboard.

|**Element**|**Responsibility**|
| :- | :- |
|QueryInputView|Displays the conversational input UI and updates when responses arrive. Embodies client-side reference architecture for UC-1.|
|DashboardView|Presents the personalized dashboard including courses, deadlines, and events. Supports UC-2.|
|QueryController|Coordinates user input processing and prepares requests to the backend for query handling.|
|DashboardController|Retrieves dashboard data from backend and updates the presentation layer. Responsible for UC-2 execution flow.|
|ClientRequestManager|Manages all outbound communication from the client to the server (API Gateway). Handles authentication tokens and request formatting.|
|RequestService (Facade)|Entry point for all client requests. Provides a unified interface for UC-1, UC-2, and UC-7.|
|ConversationController|Contains server-side conversational logic. Manages request flow to AIOrchestrator and DomainEntities for UC-1.|
|DashboardComposer|Aggregates data from external systems and mappers to generate the personalized dashboard (UC-2).|
|SyncCoordinator|Implements business logic for scheduled data synchronization, retries, and recovery (UC-7).|
|AIOrchestrator|Coordinates prompt construction, grounding, context retrieval, and model selection for AI-backed responses.|
|DomainEntities|Contains the server-side representation of domain objects (Query, AIResponse, Course, Event). Used by multiple controllers.|
|UserDataMapper|CRUD operations for user profiles, preferences, and personalization context.|
|CourseDataMapper|Persistence operations for course data retrieved from external systems.|
|EventDataMapper|CRUD operations for external events used in UC-2 and UC-7.|
|ExternalSystemConnector|Responsible for communicating with LMS, Registration, Calendar, and Email systems. Implements retries and circuit breakers.|
|VectorStoreConnector|Accesses embeddings and semantic vectors for AI contextualization. Supports UC-1 and UC-7.|

|**ProfileService**|getUserProfile(userID)|Returns student profile used for personalization.|

|Element|Method Name|Description|
| :- | :- | :- |
|SyncScheduler|triggerSync()|Periodically schedules sync job execution.|

||runFullSync()|Runs complete dataset sync (fallback on major failures).|

||enqueueRetry(item)|Sends failed items to retry queue.|

|LMSAdapter|syncCourses(cursor)|Retrieves course updates from LMS.|
|RegistrationAdapter|syncEnrollment(cursor)|Retrieves enrollment changes.|
|CalendarAdapter|syncEvents(cursor)|Retrieves event/calendar updates.|
|OperationalDB|upsert(entity)|Writes data using idempotent upsert logic.|
|VectorStore|updateEmbedding(entity)|Updates vector embeddings for search/RAG.|
|CircuitBreaker|check() / open() / close()|Ensures resilience during integration failures.|
|AnalyticsService|recordSyncOutcome(status)|Logs sync metrics, errors, and success counts.|
